PATENTS PROCESS, Inc., and Frank D. Williams, Appellants, v. Walter C. DURST, Trustee in Bankruptcy of PATENTS PROCESS, Inc., and Frank D. Williams, Bankrupts, Appellee. No. 7051. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 9, 1934. Eldred E. Wolford, Allan F. Daily, and Edward Gallaudet, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. William R. Millar, of Los Angeles, Cal, for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

After oral argument of counsel for respective parties, ordered order of District Court in this cause affirmed upon the authority of Brown v. Brown, 170 Cal. 1, 147 P. 1168; mandate forthwith.
